---
name: sprint-plan
version: 1.1.0
description: Generate a sprint plan document for atm-core phases.
format: markdown
required_variables:
  - id
  - title
  - branch
  - target
optional_variables:
  - status
  - worktree
  - goal
  - dependencies
  - exact_targets
  - deliverables
  - required_work
  - explicit_code_samples
  - non_closure
  - acceptance_criteria
  - validation
defaults:
  status: planned
  worktree: ""
  goal: []
  dependencies: []
  exact_targets: []
  deliverables: []
  required_work: []
  explicit_code_samples: []
  non_closure: []
  acceptance_criteria: []
  validation:
    - "cargo build --workspace"
    - "cargo test --workspace"
    - "cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings"
    - "git diff --check"
---
---
id: {{ id }}
title: {{ title }}
status: {{ status }}
branch: {{ branch }}
{% if worktree %}worktree: {{ worktree }}
{% endif %}target: {{ target }}
---

# Sprint {{ id }} — {{ title }}

## Goal

{% for item in goal %}- {{ item }}
{% endfor %}
## Hard Dependencies

{% for dep in dependencies %}- {{ dep }}
{% endfor %}
## Exact Targets

{% for file in exact_targets %}- `{{ file }}`
{% endfor %}
## Deliverables

Every listed deliverable is expected to land at a production-ready level for
the scope this sprint claims. If that cannot be done cleanly in one sprint, the
sprint must be split before implementation begins. No deliverable may be
silently dropped or partially deferred.

{% for item in deliverables %}- {{ item }}
{% endfor %}
## Required Work

{% for item in required_work %}- {{ item }}
{% endfor %}
## Explicit Code Samples

If the sprint introduces or changes important traits, features, enums, protocol
types, boundary contracts, or execution seams, this section must include
explicit code samples or signatures showing the intended end state.

{% for item in explicit_code_samples %}{{ item }}
{% endfor %}
## This Sprint Does Not Close

{% for item in non_closure %}- {{ item }}
{% endfor %}
## Acceptance Criteria

{% for criterion in acceptance_criteria %}- {{ criterion }}
{% endfor %}
## Required Validation

{% for cmd in validation %}- `{{ cmd }}`
{% endfor %}
